    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Environmentalists Are Wrong,'' by Bjorn Lomborg (Op-Ed, Aug. 26):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Environmentalists Are Wrong,'' by Bjorn Lomborg (Op-Ed, Aug. 26):</p>
        <p>Whatever the actual figure, the simple truth about species extinction is that many of the planet's most spectacular creatures -- mountain gorillas, tigers, pandas, orangutans and so on -- may disappear from the wild within our lifetimes. And the pandemonium of global warming will have its most devastating effects on the poor inhabitants of countries far from Mr. Lomborg in Denmark.</p>
        <p>One has only to observe the disastrous floods that have recently afflicted Asia -- the synergistic result of climate change and deforestation -- to see how the poor suffer from the folly of the rich and then strive to imitate it.</p>
        <p>DAVID HAYDEN  Wilton, Conn., Aug. 26, 2002</p>
      </block>
